                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 14.5,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has our opinion this morning in case 13-553, Alabama Department of Revenue v. CSX Transportation."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 14.5,
                        "stop": 382.119,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 14.5,
                                "stop": 21.76,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case is here on Writ of Certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.76,
                                "stop": 38.958,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The so-called 4-R Act, the Railroad Revitalization and Regulatory Reform Act of 1976 forbids the state \u201cto discriminate against a rail carrier.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.958,
                                "stop": 59.413,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case requires us to determine first whether a state violates this prohibition by requiring commercial and industrial businesses, including rail roads to pay a tax while simultaneously exempting railroads\u0027 competitors from that tax but not railroads themselves."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.413,
                                "stop": 73.947,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If so, we must then resolve whether a state may respond to such a tax discrimination claim by proving that other state tax provisions justify the differing treatment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.947,
                                "stop": 78.348,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Alabama imposes sales and use taxes on diesel fuel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.348,
                                "stop": 99.286,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It applies these taxes to railroads\u0027 purchase or sale of diesel fuel for their operations, but exempts two of the railroads competitors; trucking companies which we will call motor carriers and companies that transport goods interstate through navigable waters which we call water carriers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.286,
                                "stop": 103.843,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Motor carriers instead pay a separate fuel tax."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.843,
                                "stop": 110.157,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Water carriers pay neither sales nor use taxes on their diesel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.157,
                                "stop": 136.632,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Respondent CSX sued in District Court to enjoin petitioner Alabama from collecting sales and use taxes from it arguing that those taxes violated the 4-R Act (b) (4), a provision that prohibits states and their subunits from \u201cimposing another tax that discriminates against the rail carrier.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.632,
                                "stop": 143.714,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The District Court rejected CSX\u0027s claimed after a trial and the Eleventh Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.714,
                                "stop": 156.43,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Eleventh Circuit reasoned that CSX could bring a 4-R Act challenge alleging discrimination as against the railroads\u0027 competitors, as CSX did here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.43,
                                "stop": 169.773,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But it also rejected Alabama\u0027s response to CSX\u0027s claim namely that motor carriers are exempt from sales and use taxes because they pay a different and roughly equivalent tax."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.773,
                                "stop": 172.934,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We reverse the Eleventh Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.934,
                                "stop": 185.617,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We agree with the Eleventh Circuit that the relevant subsection of the 4-R Act subsection (b) (4) permits a claim based on discrimination against a railroad relative to its competitors."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.617,
                                "stop": 199.287,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The preceding three subsections of the act prohibit property taxes that treat railroads differently from commercial and industrial taxpayers in the jurisdiction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.287,
                                "stop": 208.192,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Subsection (b) (4) forbids imposition of \u201canother tax that discriminates against the rail carrier.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.192,
                                "stop": 224.73,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Nothing in the ordinary use of the term discriminate implies that discrimination only occurs when a railroad is singled out relative to all other commercial and industrial taxpayers which was the precise comparison required by the first three subsections."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.73,
                                "stop": 235.865,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Instead, a tax discriminates against the railroad when it treats a railroad differently from other similarly situated entities without sufficient justification."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 235.865,
                                "stop": 246.873,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We agree that for purposes of the 4-R Act the appropriate comparison for determining whether discrimination has occurred depends on the plaintiff\u0027s complaint."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.873,
                                "stop": 260.482,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The District Court must then determine if the proposed comparison class is in fact similarly situated to the railroad which is the hard requirement to comply with."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.482,
                                "stop": 264.879,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "CSX\u0027s competitors however surely are."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.879,
                                "stop": 275.912,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the Eleventh Circuit also determined that it could not consider Alabama\u0027s tax related justifications for exempting motor carriers and water carriers but not railroads."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 275.912,
                                "stop": 304,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "On this point we disagree. Just as it does not comport with ordinary English to narrow the term discrimination to only those cases where a railroad complains that it has been targeted as against all other commercial and industrial taxpayers so also it does not comport with that term\u0027s \u2018ordinary use\u0027 to describe two rival industries who pay separate but roughly comparable taxes as being discriminated against."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 304,
                                "stop": 315.496,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If that were so, both industries in such a hypothetical case could complain about being discriminated against the other."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 315.496,
                                "stop": 328.538,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our negative Commerce Clause cases also endorse the proposition that an alternative tax regime may justify a tax that would otherwise be discriminatory."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 328.538,
                                "stop": 339.682,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We do not decide whether Alabama\u0027s tax regime subjects railroads and their competitors to roughly equivalent taxes and therefore justifies railroads\u0027 different treatment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 339.682,
                                "stop": 346.417,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We leave that difficult question to the Eleventh Circuit to decide in the first instance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 346.417,
                                "stop": 362.236,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We acknowledge that the vagaries of state tax law will present challenging cases for Federal Courts but if this burden is Sisyphean, as the Eleventh Circuit called it, it is nonetheless a task that Congress has assigned to the courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 362.236,
                                "stop": 366.991,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We cannot refuse it simply because it will likely prove vexing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 366.991,
                                "stop": 374.159,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Eleventh Circuit is reversed and we remand for further proceedings consistent with our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 374.159,
                                "stop": 382.119,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Ginsburg joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
